responsibilities:
Formulates legislative initiatives for assigned issue areas which include:
1.devising a legislative plan;
2.drafting the plan into legislative form;
3.planning, coordinating and scheduling introduction of legislation in the House
(or offering it on an appropriate vehicle if it is in an amendment);
4.gathering support for a bill or amendment from other Members, as well as
appropriate interest groups;
5.working with committees on legislation;
6.coordinating legislative support to get the bill passed in the House.
